opinions.text:
ORDER
The petition for writ of habeas corpus is denied without prejudice to petitioner’s renewing his petition after his sentencing if he is denied bail at that time.

attorneys: Dennis J. Roberts II, Atty. Gen., Alan R. Tate, Asst. Atty. Gen., for plaintiff-respondent.
Charles J. Rogers, Jr., Providence, for defendant-petitioner.

STATE v. Daniel CAMPANIELLO.
No. 82-550-M.P.
Supreme Court of Rhode Island.
Dec. 30, 1982.
Dennis J. Roberts II, Atty. Gen., Alan R. Tate, Asst. Atty. Gen., for plaintiff-respondent.
Charles J. Rogers, Jr., Providence, for defendant-petitioner.
